\section*{Example 11.1}

A current of 0.5 A is drawn by a filament of an electric bulb for 10 minutes. Find the amount of electric charge that flows through the circuit.

\section*{Solution}

We are given, \(I=0.5 \mathrm{~A} ; t=10 \mathrm{~min}=600 \mathrm{~s}\).
From Eq. (11.1), we have
\[
\begin{aligned}
Q & =I t \\
& =0.5 \mathrm{~A} \times 600 \mathrm{~s} \\
& =300 \mathrm{C}
\end{aligned}
\]

